virtual ResultType EmzH264Decoder::AllocateOutputBuffers (  UINT8 &  out_buf_count,
UINT32 &  out_buf_len
)  [virtual]
 

Allocates a number of output buffers that are used to store the decoded (and post-processed) frames.

Parameters:
out_buf_count Desired number of buffers to be allocated in the output buffer array. If set to 0, the default number of buffers will be allocated. On return, the actual number of buffers, i.e. the EmzH264Decoder can adapt the number passed in by the caller if necessary.
out_buf_len Desired length (in bytes) of one output buffer (all buffers have the same length). If set to 0, the default length will be used. On return, the actual buffer length, i.e. the EmzH264Decoder can adapt the length passed in by the caller if necessary.
Returns:
Success if the operation was successful. Otherwise, an appropriate error code.

Implements VideoDecoder.

CodecDevice::ResultType EmzH264Decoder::DecodeFrame (  const UINT8 HUGE *  in_buf,
UINT32  in_buf_len,
UINT16  flags,
UINT32  time_stamp
)  [virtual]
 

Decodes a video frame. The input buffer contains always one complete frame. The actual decoding is done asynchronously, i.e., when the decoding process has finished, the callback function CbVideoFrameDecoded will be invoked.

Parameters:
in_buf Pointer to the video input buffer (containing the encoded frame).
in_buf_len Length of the video input buffer (in bytes).
flags Bit flags as defined by the FlagsType enum indicating if it is the last frame in the stream/file.
Returns:
Success if the operation was successful. Otherwise, an appropriate error code.
See also:
CbFrameDecoded

Implements VideoDecoder.

virtual ResultType EmzH264Decoder::DecodePacket (  const UINT8 HUGE *  in_buf,
UINT32  in_buf_len,
UINT16  flags
)  [virtual]
 

Decodes a video packet. Contains one or more packet but the packets are always complete. The actual decoding is done asynchronously, i.e., when a complete frame has been decoded, the callback function CbVideoFrameDecoded will be invoked.

Parameters:
in_buf Pointer to the video input buffer (containing the encoded packets)
in_buf_len Length of the video input buffer (in bytes).
flags Bit flags as defined by the FlagsType enum. It indicates if it is the last packet in the frame and if it is the last frame.
Returns:
Success if the operation was successful. Otherwise, an appropriate error code.
See also:
CbFrameDecoded

Implements VideoDecoder.

virtual ResultType EmzH264Decoder::GetParameters (  const ParameterType *  types_array,
UINT32 *  values_array,
UINT8  array_count
)  [virtual]
 

This function retrieves the values of specified parameters in the video decoder.

Parameters:
types_array Array of the parameter types that specify the parameters to be retrieved.
values_array On return, array of the retrieved parameter values. The first element in this array is of type that is specified by the first element of types_array and so on. In general, the values themselves have to be casted to the actual parameter type. The caller has to allocate memory for this array before invoking of this function. The existing elements of the array are then filled with the corresponding parameter values by the video decoder.
array_count Length (number of elements) of the types_array and types_array i.e., both arrays have always the same length.
Returns:
Success if the operation was successful. Otherwise, an appropriate error code.

virtual ResultType EmzH264Decoder::NotifyOutputBufferReleased (  const UINT8 HUGE *  out_buf  )  [virtual]
 

This function is used to notify the decoder that the specified decoder output buffer has been released (by some other entity) and can be re-used by the decoder. In general, this function is called by the client application when the buffer has been rendered and automatically released by the renderer (VideoChannel device).

Parameters:
out_buf Pointer to the video output buffer that has been released.
Returns:
Success if the operation was successful. Otherwise, an appropriate error code.

virtual ResultType EmzH264Decoder::RegisterCallbackFunctions (  void *  context,
CbFrameDecoded  cb_frame_decoded,
CbInBufferFree  cb_in_buf_free
)  [virtual]
 

Register callback functions.

Parameters:
context A context (e.g. this pointer) that is valid for all callback functions registered with this instance of the EmzH264Decoder. This context is then passed as an argument of all callback functions invoked by the EmzH264Decoder.
cb_frame_decoded A pointer to a callback function that is invoked by the EmzH264Decoder when a frame has been decoded (and post-processed) and is ready for rendering.
cb_in_buf_free A pointer to a callback function that is called by the EmzH264Decoder when a video input buffer is not used anymore by the decoder (as the data has been already decoded) and can be re-used.
Returns:
Success if the operation was successful. Otherwise, an appropriate error code.

virtual ResultType EmzH264Decoder::ReleaseOutputBuffer (  const UINT8 HUGE *  out_buf  )  [virtual]
 

Releases the specified output buffer of the decoder and, thus, allows the decoder to fill it with new decoded (and post-processed) frames if available. In general, this function is called when the frame stored in the buffer shall not been rendered at all or it has been rendered but the buffer has not been released automatically.

Parameters:
out_buf Pointer to the video decoder output buffer that shall be released.
Returns:
Success if the operation was successful. Otherwise, an appropriate error code.
See also:
NotifyOutputBufferReleased
